2.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> I got into a somewhat lengthy discussion with my guild about the use of spirit of the cheetah.  A lot of people (non-druids who never had to run from anything i guess) said its a worthless spell and they dont even bother buying it.  I however disagree.  It is the only spell i have at all times mem'ed in an outdoor enviroment.  Reason being is...it has a EXTREMELY short cast time.  (with the right timing you can almost cast it on the run, the cast time is so low)  it last 45 seconds and you travel at mach 3.  I have yet to SoC out of a situation and later the mob caught up to me...well thats not true, grimfeather, but that is a different story.  I want the general opinion of what i think is a important spell in my book. Yay or nay ? <p>Greystone Thorngage 39 Druid <BR>
Roundtom Birglechirp Warrior 16 <BR>
<BR>

"Lo there do I see my father. Lo there do I see my mother, my sisters, and my brothers. Lo there do I see the line of my people, back to the beginning. Lo they do call me. They bid me take my place among them in the halls of Valhalla. Where the brave, may live forever"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ueeri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eeri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 5:54:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> The only time I have ever used that spell was for crossing West Karana to get to Q Hills. Damn was it a long walk <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203259">Vinre, 55 Cleric</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133147">Eeri Spiritguide, Oracle</a><br><a href="http://www.skip.informatik.gu.se/~fjutt/nathaq/">Nathaq</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umandari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 6:18:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.nc.rr.com/prismites/icon1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> In my younger days when I hunted Rathe Mtns I had it mem'd all the time as an escape mechanism.  The scattered corpses of fallen druids suggest they might reconsider the spell's worth (and suggest divine justice at work).  <br>
<br>
Now I just use it to cross West Karana. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p>Thormir Anvilheart
<br>Oracle
<br>Leader of <A HREF="http://home.nc.rr.com/prismites">PRISM</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umalse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 6:37:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> I think I've cast that spell exactly once across all the characters that could scribe it, and that was to test what it did.<br>
<br>
Huge recast times combined with mostly dungeon fighting make for a page 40 candidate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ushenlong495.showPublicProfile?language=EN>shenlong495</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 7:15:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> its a very useful spell for pvp, but then again we are talking ayonae, so meh...<br>
<br>
I still keep it memmed always, out of habbit, and it has saved me afew times. other uses for it, if you use soc, 4/5 times it takes you out of aggro range of the mob. also useful for sprints through a kos zone, etc.<br>
<br>
well worth the money paid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubdnightfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BD Nightfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 7:38:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> I hardly bothered with the spell.  It has too long a recast time for me to want to waste a spell slot for it.  Like someone else said, one of the only times I used it was getting across WK lol. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukanyli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanyli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 7:58:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/attacca/selfportrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> Some folks swear by it, some swear against it.  Personally, I was never a big fan.  But I'm pretty fast as it is in say wolf form.  If it's your thing, go for it, personally I liked freeing up the spell slot.<br>
<br>
Very few things will outrun SoW at the appropriate level.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Kanyli <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ushenlong495.showPublicProfile?language=EN>shenlong495</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 8:21:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> soc outruns sow about 3 times over. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugreystonethorngage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GreystoneThorngage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/3/02 8:30:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2717.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of the Cheetah (not a topic about whose faster)</span><hr size=1> if i had a nickel for everytime that spell saved my life, i'd be rich <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  cliche yes, but trune none the less <p>Greystone Thorngage 39 Druid <BR>
